</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhatha>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Animist of Shar Vahl<br>The Dark Side wants YOU!</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/02 10:53:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> Lots of MR is a good start.  If you get slowed, debuffed, blinded constantly, you're going to have a tough time winning.  Also, were you in an arena or using /duel?  In /duel we cannot cast any beneficial spells on others.... <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>including our pet</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> so debuffing with a clicky or even killing the pet becomes an option when we can't heal it.  Different story in an arena.  Really depends what gear each of you have too, and what buffs.<br>
<br>
Basically, you have the complications of a pet chewing you up, usually stunning from the backside unless you do something about it... the bst themselves who can joust you while this is going on, and a compliment of spells, mostly magic based, but also various dots and cold nukes up to 450.<br>
<br>
I don't know a heck of a lot about dueling but if ya want practice shoot me tell sometime. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END-->[A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalninil@firionavie>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 661<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/02 12:10:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> Ok i haven't faught a beastlord but hear is my assumption<br>
<br>
1. beastlords have sow , to stand a chance you need to have Sow ( potions not jboots, jboots are slower than sow ) or a horse faster than sow.<br>
<br>
2. beastlords have invis , to stand a chance you need to have a see invis item of some type<br>
<br>
3. beastlords have a good selection of magic, cold, poisin, and disease , you need to have 120 + resists in at least cold and magic, along with cure poisin/disease potions.<br>
<br>
4. beastlords are able to heal there pets at a great mana effieicney and have mana regen, so no matter how much they  hurt you have to concentrate on the beastlord<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakanome>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 487<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/02 12:58:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> Get a SoW potion.  Get a big 2 hander (delay is not worth the bother, for once, big hits are worth a damn, double 100s really, really hurt).  Debuff then ignore the pet, no matter how much he is hurting.  Get resists (those awful nukes they have are hell).  Try not to let the beastlord cast any spells at all, make him run from you and try and angle his warder so he and his warder are hammering on you from the same side (simple stuff but if you miss it during battle it hurts something fierce).  If he starts meleeing you full on, switch to your one handers and wail on him.  If the beastlord is being forced to fight you head on, you will probably kill him with luck (especially with a damage shield).  If he's running, you'll have to be as fast or faster than him, otherwise he'll kill you, if you're faster, you'll kill him.  Try a damage shield and don't let them debuff you at all.<br>
<br>
Never attack the pet.  They heal their pets far too efficiently for it to be worth the bother. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarkellraven>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed of Bristlebane</span><br>  Posts: 1702<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/02 3:37:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> Blind, Fear, or Root the pet.  You want that thing out of your way.  I use blind poisons myself if prepared.  Make sure your resists are in the 150s or so.  That's pretty standard dueling proceedure.  You don't want to be chain blinded.  <br>
<br>
If you can snare the beastlord, that's WONDERFUL.  Makes him much easier to whack.  But in the end it comes down to how well and fast you can joust him.  Run up, attack once, run back or through. <br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bloodandsin>bloodandsin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/02 9:40:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> Damage shield (8th coldain ring) and let the pet slowly die while its wacking you and your wacking the BL.<br>
