<br>
Nukes are cold based.<br>
<br>
We have one, count it, one disease dot, sicken, pre 60, after that scourge comes into play.<br>
<br>
Poison dot up to 400ish (venom of the snake).<br>
<br>
Magic resist for slows, debuffs, blind.<br>
<br>
Pet procs can be based off of any resist type we choose, max of 141 damage per proc.  A few of the higher procs have a small stun component.<br>
<br>
<br>
Part of the problem is that, even being out for a year, lots of people don't know what we can do or how we fight in general, at least not at the high end, looking at spell list is not as good as grouping, but there are so few at high end that it becomes difficult.  I have always tried to show people how we work but I get the idea that too many people say &quot;BL crack&quot; and ignore the rest.. bleh.  Low end is another story. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhatha>Rhatha</A> at: 11/15/02 1:55:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalninil@firionavie>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 670<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/02 3:48:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a BL</span><hr size=1> BL crack <br>
