t would take many, many dispells to kill off the important buffs.  Even if you strip four at a time, and they only have one clicker, that's 4 or 5 dispells.  It would work, and if you hit the right buffs it would work very well, but the balance is the time needed to get those buffs while the pet is gnawing on you and the bst is either in melee or tossing spells at you.<br>
<br>
Agreed on one point though, in any duel, the person with the best toys has a big advantage. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438">Rhatha Sha`Naya</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and Swiftclaw<br>
